2.name: hide.bs.tooltip
2.description: This event is fired immediately when the hide instance method has been called.

3.name: hidden.bs.tooltip
3.description: This event is fired when the tooltip has finished being hidden from the user (will wait for CSS transitions to complete).

4.name: inserted.bs.tooltip
4.description: This event is fired after the show.bs.tooltip event when the tooltip template has been added to the DOM.

5.name: inserted.bs.tooltip
5.description: This event is fired after the show.bs.tooltip event when the tooltip template has been added to the DOM.

6.name: show.bs.tooltip
6.description: This event fires immediately when the show instance method is called.

7.name: shown.bs.tooltip
7.description: This event is fired when the tooltip has been made visible to the user (will wait for CSS transitions to complete).
